songs.title: Love on the Brain (Cover)
songs.lyrics:
[Verse: Jesy Nelson, All & Jade Thirlwall]
And you got me like, "Oh (Ooh, ooh), what you (Ooh) want from me?"
(What you want from me?)
And I tried (Ooh) to buy your (Ooh) pretty heart, but the price too (Ooh) high
Baby, you got me like (Ooh, ooh, ooh) "Ah"
You love when I (Ooh) fall apart (When I fall apart)
So you can (Ooh) put me together and (Ooh) throw me against the (Ooh) wall

[Pre-Chorus: All, Jade Thirlwall & Leigh-Anne Pinnock]
Baby, you got me like ah-ah-ah-ah-ah-ah-ah-ah (Woo)
Ah-ah-ah-ah-ah-ah-ah-ah
Don't you stop loving me (Loving me)
Don't quit loving me (Don't quit loving me)
Just start loving me (Just start loving me)
Oh, whoa, whoa, oh

[Chorus: Jesy Nelson, with Jade Thirlwall, Leigh-Anne Pinnock, Perrie Edwards & (All)]
And babe, I’m fist-fighting with fire
Just to get close to you
Can we burn something, babe?
I run for miles just to get a ta-a-a-a-aste
Must be love on the brain (Woo)
That’s got me feeling (Feeling) this way (This way)
It beats (Ooh) me black and (Ooh) blue, but it (Ooh) loves me so (Ooh) good
N' I (Oooh) can't get enough
Must be love on the bra-a-in
And it keeps cursin' my name (Cursin' my name)
No matter what I do, I’m no good without you
And I can’t get enough
Oh, whoa, ooh

[Chorus Reprise: Jesy Nelson, Jade Thirlwall, All, Perrie Edwards]
And babe, I’m fist-fighting with fire
Just to get close to you
Can we burn something, babe?
I, I run from miles just to get a ta-a-a-a-a-a-a-a-a-aste
Must be lo-o-o-o-ove on the bra-a-a (Woo) ain
Feeling this way
It beats me black and (Ooh) blue, but it (Ooh) loves me so (Ooh) good
N' I (Oooh) can't get enough
Must be love on the brain (Yeah, eh, yeah)

[Outro: Leigh-Anne Pinnock, Perrie Edwards + Jade Thirlwall with Leigh-Anne Pinnock & Jesy Nelson]
I'm no good without you
Must be love
Must be love on the brain
